{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012vn3AEZE2Zkum2nsjqKreA","type":"tool_result","content":"   770→| 6 | Attribute the `unknown` cost bucket ($175.08) — identify what generated those 878 calls | MEDIUM | NEW |\n   771→| 7 | Make `sprint-state.json` read-only after sprint completion | LOW | OPEN | 8 |\n   772→| 8 | Clean up `1-1-foo` phantom references ($24.35 wasted) | LOW | OPEN | 33+ |\n   773→\n   774→### Verdict\n   775→\n   776→Stop Ralph. 43 no-op sessions. ~$93-129 burned on nothing. Combined with the phantom story and unattributed overhead, total identifiable waste is $117-153 — up to 21% of the $736.21 sprint budget.\n   777→\n   778→The sprint is done. It has been done for 43 sessions. There are zero actionable stories. Ralph has no sprint-complete exit condition and will loop indefinitely, burning ~$2.35 per iteration. 9 iterations ran today alone.\n   779→\n   780→This is the 43rd retro saying the same thing. The retro mechanism cannot stop Ralph. Only killing the process or adding an exit condition will break the loop.\n   781→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01QG642JrSPAWw4HDFJ8bezX","session_id":"a168b15c-ec64-44b3-89ac-e9f9d9e07ae8","uuid":"82c96d44-664b-4e33-9d91-16769a26650a","timestamp":"2026-03-28T05:51:03.084Z"}
